        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 15 at 4:57PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 457 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 15
miles northeast of Clayton, or 5 miles south of Highlands, moving
southeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Highlands and Pine Mountain.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
